description: Data was loaded from GO Consortium on April 2016. GO Annotations for Homo sapiens was loaded from GO Consortium's downloader. More details: http: current.geneontology.org/products/pages/downloads.html

fields.description: Refers to the database from which the identifier in DB object ID is drawn. Example: UniProtKB
fields.name: DB

fields.description: A unique identifier from the database in DB (column 1) for the item being annotated. Examples: P09622, Q16760
fields.name: DB_Object_ID

fields.description: A (unique and valid) symbol to which DB object ID is matched. Examples: TAAR5, ID1, AIRE, MYB
fields.name: DB_Object_Symbol

fields.description: Flags that modify the interpretation of an annotation. Examples:contributes_to, NOT, colocalizes_with,NOT|contributes_to, NOT|colocalizes,null
fields.name: Qualifier

fields.description: The GO identifier for the term attributed to the DB object ID.Examples: GO:0009967,GO:0046339
fields.name: GO_ID

fields.description: One or more unique identifiers for a single source cited as an authority for the attribution of the GO ID to the DB object ID. This may be a literature reference or a database record. Examples: PMID:15718104, GO_REF:0000036
fields.name: DB_Reference

fields.description: See the GO evidence code guide for the list of valid evidence codes for GO annotationsat http://geneontology.org/page/guide-go-evidence-codesExamples: IC, ND, EXP, IBA, IDA, IEA, IEP, IGI, IKR, IMP, IPI, ISS, NAS, TAS
fields.name: Evidence_Code

fields.description: Also referred to as with, from or the with/from column. Examples: GO:0004930, GO:0000977|GO:0045944
fields.name: With_or_From

fields.description: Refers to the namespace or ontology to which the GO IDbelongs; one of P (biological process), F (molecular function) or C (cellular component). That is, either P, F, or C.
fields.name: Aspect

fields.description: Name of gene or gene product. Examples: Dihydrolipoyl dehydrogenase, mitochondrial, DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-1, Transcriptional activator GLI3
fields.name: DB_Object_Name

fields.description: Gene symbol [or other text] Note that we strongly recommend that gene synonyms are included in the gene association file, as this aids the searching of GO.Examples: TAAR5_HUMAN|TAAR5|PNR,D3_HUMAN|ID3|1R21|BHLHB25|HEIR1,MYB_HUMAN|MYB
fields.name: DB_Object_Synonym

fields.description: A description of the type of gene product being annotated. Example: protein
fields.name: DB_Object_Type

fields.description: Date on which the annotation was made; format is YYYYMMDD
fields.name: Date

fields.description: The database which made the annotation. Examples: GDB, GOC, MGI, HCNC, AgBase, UniProt, NTNU_SB, BHF-UCL, Reactome, SGD, CACAO, GO_Central, WormBase, FlyBase, Ensembl, InterPro, InAct
fields.name: Assigned_By
